---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Privacy Policy for Open Medical Skills — learn about our data collection practices, cookie usage, medical data handling, and HIPAA compliance stance."
>
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 py-16 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-4xl dark:text-white">
      Privacy Policy
    </h1>

    <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">
      Last updated: March 8, 2026
    </p>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-8 text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 leading-7">

      <!-- Introduction -->
      <section>
        <p>
          Open Medical Skills is a project of <strong>IntelMedica.ai</strong>, a company founded by a physician.
          We are committed to protecting your privacy and being transparent about our data practices. This Privacy
          Policy explains what data we collect (spoiler: almost nothing), how we use it, and your rights regarding that data.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- TL;DR Box -->
      <section>
        <div class="rounded-lg border border-cyan-800/50 bg-cyan-950/30 p-5">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-cyan-300">TL;DR — The Short Version</p>
          <ul class="mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm text-cyan-200/80">
            <li>We <strong>do not store</strong> your personal data</li>
            <li>We <strong>do not sell</strong> your data to anyone, ever</li>
            <li>We <strong>do not track</strong> you across the web</li>
            <li>We <strong>do not use</strong> advertising cookies or pixels</li>
            <li>We <strong>do not collect</strong> patient data or PHI</li>
            <li>Your theme preference lives in <code class="rounded bg-cyan-900/50 px-1 text-[11px]">localStorage</code> on your device — it never leaves your browser</li>
            <li>We are physicians, not advertisers. Your privacy is safe with us.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 1. What We Collect -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">1. What Data We Collect</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Open Medical Skills is a <strong>static directory website</strong> — we catalog medical AI skills and plugins,
          but we do not require user accounts, logins, or any personally identifiable information (PII) to browse the directory.
        </p>

        <h3 class="mt-6 text-lg font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white">1.1 Data We Do NOT Collect</h3>
        <p class="mt-2">Let us be crystal clear about what we do <strong>not</strong> collect:</p>
        <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li>Names, email addresses, phone numbers, or mailing addresses</li>
          <li>Usernames or passwords (we have no user accounts)</li>
          <li>Payment or financial information</li>
          <li>Patient data, medical records, or Protected Health Information (PHI)</li>
          <li>Biometric data, health data, or genetic information</li>
          <li>Social Security numbers or government-issued IDs</li>
          <li>Browser fingerprints, device IDs, or advertising identifiers</li>
          <li>Keystroke logs, session recordings, or mouse tracking data</li>
          <li>Cross-site tracking data or third-party advertising cookies</li>
        </ul>

        <h3 class="mt-6 text-lg font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white">1.2 Analytics Data (Anonymous, If Enabled)</h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          We may use privacy-focused web analytics (such as Plausible or similar privacy-first tools) to understand
          general site usage patterns. If enabled, this may include:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li>Page views and navigation paths (aggregated, not per-user)</li>
          <li>Referral sources (where visitors came from)</li>
          <li>Device type and browser family (aggregated, not user-specific)</li>
          <li>General geographic region (country-level only, no IP logging)</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-2">
          We <strong>do not</strong> use Google Analytics, Facebook Pixel, or any invasive tracking, cross-site cookies,
          or fingerprinting technologies. Ever.
        </p>

        <h3 class="mt-6 text-lg font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white">1.3 Theme Preference (Local Storage Only)</h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          Your dark mode / light mode preference is stored in your browser's <code class="rounded bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-sm dark:bg-slate-800">localStorage</code>.
          This data <strong>never leaves your device</strong>, is not transmitted to any server, and cannot be read by us or anyone else.
        </p>

        <h3 class="mt-6 text-lg font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white">1.4 Cookie Consent Preference (Local Storage Only)</h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          When you interact with our cookie banner, your choice is stored in <code class="rounded bg-slate-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-sm dark:bg-slate-800">localStorage</code>
          so we don't show it again. Like your theme preference, this never leaves your browser.
        </p>

        <h3 class="mt-6 text-lg font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white">1.5 GitHub Submissions</h3>
        <p class="mt-2">
          If you submit a skill or plugin via GitHub pull request or our web form, your submission will be publicly
          visible on GitHub. Your GitHub username and any information you include in the submission will be part of
          the public repository history. This is governed by <strong>GitHub's privacy policy</strong>, not ours.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 2. Data Storage -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">2. Data Storage and Retention</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 rounded-lg border border-emerald-800/50 bg-emerald-950/30 p-4">
          <p class="font-medium text-emerald-300">We Do Not Store Your Data</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-emerald-200/80">
            Open Medical Skills is a <strong>static website</strong> served via a CDN. We have no user database,
            no server-side sessions, no analytics database that stores individual user data, and no mechanism to
            identify returning visitors. There is no data to retain because there is no data to collect.
          </p>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-4">
          If we introduce user accounts or personalized features in the future, we will update this policy
          <strong>before</strong> collecting any new data and will require fresh consent.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 3. Patient Data & PHI -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">3. Patient Data and Protected Health Information (PHI)</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Open Medical Skills is a <strong>directory of tools</strong> — we do not collect, process, store, transmit,
          or have access to any patient data or Protected Health Information (PHI). We are <strong>not a covered entity</strong>
          and <strong>not a business associate</strong> under HIPAA.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Each listed skill is an independent third-party project with its own data handling practices.
          <strong>You are solely responsible for reviewing the privacy policy, data handling practices, and compliance posture
          of any skill or plugin before deploying it in a clinical, research, or production environment.</strong>
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4">
          We strongly recommend that healthcare professionals and organizations:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li>Conduct independent security and privacy assessments before deploying any tool with patient data</li>
          <li>Ensure any skill handling PHI has a valid Business Associate Agreement (BAA) with the skill provider</li>
          <li>Follow your organization's data governance and information security policies</li>
          <li>Comply with HIPAA, HITECH, state privacy laws, and institutional review board (IRB) requirements where applicable</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- 4. Cookies -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">4. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Here is our complete, exhaustive list of cookies and storage technologies:
        </p>
        <div class="mt-4 overflow-x-auto">
          <table class="min-w-full text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="border-b border-slate-700">
                <th class="py-2 pr-4 text-left font-medium text-slate-300">Technology</th>
                <th class="py-2 pr-4 text-left font-medium text-slate-300">Purpose</th>
                <th class="py-2 pr-4 text-left font-medium text-slate-300">Duration</th>
                <th class="py-2 text-left font-medium text-slate-300">Sent to Server?</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody class="text-slate-400">
              <tr class="border-b border-slate-800">
                <td class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-xs text-cyan-400">localStorage: theme</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">Dark/light mode preference</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">Until you clear it</td>
                <td class="py-2">No</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-slate-800">
                <td class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-xs text-cyan-400">localStorage: oms-cookie-ok</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">Cookie banner dismissal</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">Until you clear it</td>
                <td class="py-2">No</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-slate-800">
                <td class="py-2 pr-4 font-mono text-xs text-cyan-400">Cloudflare cookies</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">DDoS protection, bot detection</td>
                <td class="py-2 pr-4">Session</td>
                <td class="py-2">To Cloudflare only</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
        <p class="mt-4">
          That's it. That's the whole list. We <strong>do not embed</strong> third-party trackers, ad networks,
          social media pixels, remarketing tags, or any other tracking technology.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-3">
          You can disable cookies in your browser settings or clear localStorage at any time. Doing so will not
          affect your ability to browse the directory.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 5. Third-Party Services -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">5. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          We rely on a minimal set of third-party services:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li>
            <strong>Cloudflare Pages</strong>: Our website is hosted on Cloudflare's CDN for performance, security,
            and DDoS protection. Cloudflare may log basic request metadata (IP addresses, timestamps) for security
            purposes, subject to <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" class="text-primary hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cloudflare's Privacy Policy</a>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>GitHub</strong>: Skill submissions, pull requests, and issue tracking are hosted on GitHub.
            <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement" class="text-primary hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub's Privacy Statement</a> applies to any data you submit via GitHub.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Google Fonts</strong>: We load the Inter and JetBrains Mono fonts from Google Fonts. Google may
            log basic request data. No cookies are set by Google Fonts.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4">
          We do <strong>not</strong> use: Google Analytics, Facebook/Meta SDKs, Hotjar, Mixpanel, Segment, Amplitude,
          or any other user behavior tracking service.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 6. Data Sharing and Selling -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">6. Data Sharing and Selling</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 rounded-lg border border-emerald-800/50 bg-emerald-950/30 p-4">
          <p class="font-medium text-emerald-300">We Do Not Sell Your Data. Period.</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-emerald-200/80">
            We do not sell, rent, lease, trade, or otherwise transfer any user data to third parties for any reason —
            commercial, marketing, analytics, or otherwise. Since we don't collect personal data, there is nothing to sell.
            This is not just a policy, it's a structural impossibility. You can't sell what you don't have.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 7. Medical Disclaimer -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">7. Medical Disclaimer</h2>
        <div class="mt-4 rounded-lg border border-amber-200 bg-amber-50 p-4 dark:border-amber-800/50 dark:bg-amber-950/30">
          <p class="font-medium text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-200">Important Medical Disclaimer</p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-200">
            Open Medical Skills is a <strong>directory of tools</strong> — it does not provide medical advice,
            diagnosis, or treatment. The skills listed here are third-party software tools intended to assist
            healthcare professionals. They are <strong>not medical devices</strong> (unless explicitly stated and
            FDA-cleared) and do not replace clinical judgment, medical training, or the physician-patient relationship.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- 8. HIPAA Disclaimer -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">8. HIPAA Compliance Stance</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Open Medical Skills is a <strong>publicly accessible directory website</strong>. We are not a covered entity
          or business associate under the Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA). We do not handle
          PHI or enter into Business Associate Agreements (BAAs).
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4">
          If you deploy a skill from this directory in a HIPAA-regulated environment, you are responsible for ensuring
          that the skill's author has appropriate compliance measures in place and that you execute any necessary BAAs
          with the skill provider.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 9. Your Rights -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">9. Your Privacy Rights</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Depending on your location, you may have rights under data protection laws such as GDPR (Europe), CCPA/CPRA
          (California), LGPD (Brazil), PIPEDA (Canada), or similar regulations. These typically include the right to:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-2 list-disc pl-6 space-y-1">
          <li>Access any personal data we hold about you</li>
          <li>Request deletion of your personal data</li>
          <li>Opt out of the sale of personal data</li>
          <li>Request data portability</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Because we do not collect PII, these rights are largely not applicable to our current operations. However,
          we respect your rights and will comply with any valid request. Contact us if you have questions.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 10. Children's Privacy -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">10. Children's Privacy</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Open Medical Skills is not directed at children under the age of 13 (or 16 in the EU). We do not knowingly
          collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has submitted information to us, please
          contact us immediately.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 11. International Users -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">11. International Users</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          Open Medical Skills is accessible worldwide. If you access the site from outside the United States, you
          acknowledge that any data you submit (e.g., via GitHub) may be processed and stored in the United States
          or other jurisdictions where our service providers operate. Our CDN (Cloudflare) serves content from
          edge locations globally.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 12. Changes to This Policy -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">12. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements.
          Updates will be posted on this page with a new "Last updated" date. Your continued use of the site after
          changes are posted constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-4">
          If we ever begin collecting personal data (e.g., through user accounts), we will notify users prominently
          and require fresh consent before any new data collection begins.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 13. Contact -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-white">13. Contact Information</h2>
        <p class="mt-4">
          If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact:
        </p>
        <div class="mt-4 rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50 p-4 dark:border-slate-800 dark:bg-slate-900/50">
          <p class="font-medium text-slate-900 dark:text-white">IntelMedica.ai</p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm">Email: <a href="mailto:privacy@intelmedica.ai" class="text-primary hover:underline">privacy@intelmedica.ai</a></p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm">GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/IntelMedica" class="text-primary hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">IntelMedica</a></p>
          <p class="mt-1 text-sm">Hugging Face: <a href="https://huggingface.co/intelmedica" class="text-primary hover:underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener">intelmedica</a></p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Footer Note -->
      <section class="mt-12 border-t border-slate-200 pt-8 dark:border-slate-800">
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-500">
          <strong>Open Medical Skills</strong> is a project of <strong>IntelMedica.ai</strong>, founded by a physician.
          We are committed to transparency, privacy, and building tools that serve the healthcare community responsibly.
        </p>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
